The paper deals with automating the interpretation of ultrasound videos for measuring carotid intima-media thickness (CIMT) using convolutional neural networks (CNNs). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves extensive experiments and the use of CNNs, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with medical imaging and healthcare, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper deals with cardiovascular disease, which could place it in cs.BIO (Computational Biology).
